HEADWORD: Knicker
<hw>Knick"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>knikker</ets>.]</ety> <def>A small ball of clay, baked hard and
oiled, used as a marble by boys in playing.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & U.
S.]</mark> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au> <au>Bartlett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

